article.headline: Albany 69, New Hampshire 52
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Jamar Wilson scored 20 points to lead Albany in a 69-52 win over New Hampshire Wednesday night. Albany (8-5, 1-0 America East) has won six of the last seven away games. Jason Siggers had 16 points for Albany, Brent Wilson added 10. Jermaine Anderson led New Hampshire (3-10, 0-1) with 18 points. Blagoj Janev contributed 13 points and Mike Christensen added 11. The Wildcats were held to 40.9 percent shooting overall, while Albany managed a 50.9 percent final shooting average. Albany outrebounded New Hampshire 38-20.
